details.description: The cargo ship was last spotted at [COORD] near a gas giant. We should be able to find its manifest on board.
Some of the spilled cargo contain an unstable material. We should carefully try to clear as many as we can.
Report to Maia Station immediately for new orders.
We should head to Celaeno Station and update the Commodore on what happened.
Evacuate the outpost on the inner planet at [COORD]
We should return the outpost crew to Celaeno for evaluation and debriefing.
We've analyzed some kind of alien navigation device uncovered by the outpost team.
Cdre. Yu wants us to investigate the planet at [COORD] where activity was detected.
We should use the nearby gateway to try to reach the region at [COORD].
Dr. Rama believes we should now be able to interface with the gateway artifact.

currentEnding.title: Vessel Lost
currentEnding.text: [SHIP_NAME] was lost while on a routine mission. The cause of the incident is still under investigation.

entries.summary: "I've received our first set of orders. A vessel was damaged by debris from a..."
entries.intro: The Argo: 2641.11.14 12:56 at -16.70 x -7.81 Starcom Space, Crew Log Entry
entries.details:
Lt. Avery:

I've received our first set of orders. A vessel was damaged by debris from a wrecked cargo ship.

I'm marking the location on your HUD.

entries.summary: "You can review mission details as well as other ship information in the..."
entries.intro: The Argo: 2641.11.14 14:10 at -16.59 x -7.68 Starcom Space, Crew Log Entry
entries.details:
Lt. Avery:

You can review mission details as well as other ship information in the ship's console.

entries.summary: Alongside the disabled vessel, The Argo downloads the cargo manifest declaration
entries.intro: 11/14/2641 2:30:00 PM The Argo Spaced-based Anomaly Report at -16.59 x -7.68 Starcom Space
entries.details:
Alongside the disabled vessel, The Argo downloads the cargo manifest declaration.

"Cargo contents: misc. waste collected from regional Starcom bases, including:

Abandoned personal effects 
Growing soil with heavy metal contaminants
Non-recoverable technical equipment
Deteriorating Xenium from experiments (Classified, caution: Extremely Volatile)"

entries.summary: "We're closing on the vessel. Looks like there are several dozen containers..."
entries.intro: The Argo: 2641.11.14 14:34 at -16.59 x -7.68 Starcom Space, Crew Log Entry
entries.details:
Lt. Avery:

We're closing on the vessel. Looks like there are several dozen containers loose. I suggest we approach with caution until we know what's in them.

entries.summary: "I'm getting a priority emergency beacon on the Starcom open hyperwave. It's..."
entries.intro: The Argo: 2641.11.14 15:13 at -16.59 x -7.68 Starcom Space, Crew Log Entry
entries.details:
Lt. Avery:

I'm getting a priority emergency beacon on the Starcom open hyperwave. It's from Maia Station: they're asking any nearby ships to report immediately.

Looks like this cleanup operation will have to wait.

entries.summary: "Degraded Xenium is dangerous stuff. We should try to destroy the loose..."
entries.intro: The Argo: 2641.11.14 15:44 at -16.70 x -7.47 Starcom Space, Crew Log Entry
entries.details:
Lt. Avery:

Degraded Xenium is dangerous stuff.  We should try to destroy the loose containers... carefully.

entries.summary: Cdre. Schell: "Thank you for responding to our priority message. Normally...
entries.intro: 11/14/2641 3:40:00 PM The Argo Comms Log Transcript
entries.details: Cdre. Schell: "Thank you for responding to our priority message. Normally this would go through Starcom Fleet HQ, but we have an urgent situation." Cdre. Schell: "We've received an emergency beacon from our outpost on the other side of a quantum wormhole. They must have a critical emergency. I need you to activate the two nearby neutrino generators that will expand the wormhole large enough for us to get through to them." Cdre. Schell: "I know you haven't been briefed on this, but our support ship was damaged by debris and is en route to Merope for repairs. Any questions?" Cmd Smith: No sir, we'll activate those generators right away. Cdre. Schell: "Glad to hear it. I'm transmitting the override codes to you now. You'll just need to get close enough to them. I should say that this project is classified. Report back once the wormhole is open and I'll fill you in on what you are permitted to discuss."

entries.summary: "We can destroy the containers with our plasma cannon"
entries.intro: The Argo: 2641.11.14 16:13 at -16.70 x -7.47 Starcom Space, Crew Log Entry
entries.details:
Lt. Avery:

We can destroy the containers with our plasma cannon.

Again, I'd suggest keeping as much distance as possible.

entries.summary: "That's one of the stabilizers."
entries.intro: The Argo: 2641.11.14 16:32 at -16.70 x -7.47 Starcom Space, Crew Log Entry
entries.details:
Lt. Avery:

That's one of the stabilizers. 

That thing is putting out a huge amount of energy. I'm reading over 800 terawatts.

entries.summary: "That shockwave knocked out bridge control. I'm trying to restart our systems."
entries.intro: The Argo: 2641.11.14 16:52 at -16.70 x -7.47 Starcom Space, Crew Log Entry
entries.details:
Lt. Avery:

That shockwave knocked out bridge control. I'm trying to restart our systems.

entries.summary: "What the fleck! Whoever or whatever that is just punched through Maia..."
entries.intro: The Argo: 2641.11.14 18:43 at -16.69 x -7.49 Starcom Space, Crew Log Entry
entries.details:
Lt. Avery:

What the fleck! Whoever or whatever that is just punched through Maia Station like their neutronium hull was aluminum.

Re-routing helm control to auxiliary, just a few more seconds...

entries.summary: "Sensors show that the warp field holding the wormhole open is collapsing."
entries.intro: The Argo: 2641.11.16 02:15 at 5.29 x 5.22 Unknown Space, Crew Log Entry
entries.details:
Lt. Avery:

Sensors show that the warp field holding the wormhole open is collapsing.

entries.summary: "Gravimetric scans show the wormhole is still there, but it's collapsed down..."
entries.intro: The Argo: 2641.11.16 03:23 at 5.29 x 5.22 Unknown Space, Crew Log Entry
entries.details:
Lt. Avery:

Gravimetric scans show the wormhole is still there, but it's collapsed down to Planck scale.

entries.summary: "I've detected a Starcom beacon on our scanners. I've marked its position in..."
entries.intro: The Argo: 2641.11.16 04:00 at 5.29 x 5.22 Unknown Space, Crew Log Entry
entries.details:
Lt. Avery:

I've detected a Starcom beacon on our scanners. I've marked its position in your HUD.

That must be the station that Maia's commander mentioned. We should make contact with them and let them know what has happened.

entries.summary: Cdre. Yu: "Welcome to Celaeno Station commander.
entries.intro: 11/16/2641 4:20:00 AM The Argo Comms Log Transcript
entries.details: Cdre. Yu: "Welcome to Celaeno Station commander. I assume your appearance means Maia picked up our emergency beacon. And I hope The Argo is just the very small tip of a much larger spear of reinforcements coming soon?" Cmd Smith: Not exactly, no. Cdre. Yu: "That sounds ominous. Go on." Cmd Smith: Fill the Commodore in on what happened. Cdre. Yu: "That's very alarming. The reason we sent the emergency beacon is that recently we've come under attack by vessels of unknown origin. We're calling them "Red Raiders" based on their markings for lack of any other information. Now you're telling me there's another threat that's cut us off from support." Cdre. Yu: "For now, there doesn't seem to be anything that can be done about Maia Station or the ship that destroyed it. But we can deal with the ships that have been attacking us. They're not terribly powerful and Celaeno's guns have kept them at bay. We have a research outpost under development on an inner planet. The only other support ship on this side of the wormhole is out of comms range. Given these attacks and the lack of imminent reinforcements, I'll need your help evacuating the staff back to the station. " Cmd Smith: Can do. Cdre. Yu: "That's what I hoped. You'll need a survey lander. I've had Lt. Milton start making modifications on The Argo. See him in the Shipyard and then get our people back safe."

entries.summary: "As per Cdre Yu's orders, I've gotten The Argo a bit more combat-ready, but..."
entries.intro: The Argo: 2641.11.16 04:23 at 5.50 x 5.50 Unknown Space, Crew Log Entry
entries.details:
Lt. Milton:

As per Cdre Yu's orders, I've gotten The Argo a bit more combat-ready, but it still needs a survey lander. Select "Utilities" from the module category list, then click drag a lander.

entries.summary: "Hostile ships detected. Weapons ready."
entries.intro: The Argo: 2641.11.16 04:32 at 5.45 x 5.46 Unknown Space, Crew Log Entry
entries.details:
Lt. Avery:

Hostile ships detected. Weapons ready.

entries.summary: The ground team is disappointed to abandon the outpost; they had been...
entries.intro: 11/16/2641 4:50:00 AM The Argo Lander SCS-01 Planetary Anomaly Report at 5.45 x 5.47 Unknown Space
entries.details:
The ground team is disappointed to abandon the outpost; they had been excavating the ruins of a civilization during a late period of the "Fallen Empire". The team had just uncovered an artifact with markings similar to the great structure in space near Celaeno.

But they quickly and professionally evacuate the object and vital materials to the lander.

entries.summary: "The team is eager to learn more about the artifact they found"
entries.intro: The Argo: 2641.11.16 05:33 at 5.45 x 5.47 Unknown Space, Crew Log Entry
entries.details:
Lt. Avery:

The team is eager to learn more about the artifact they found.

You can order an analysis from the "Cargo" tab of the ship status display.

entries.summary: Cdre. Yu: "Well done, Smith
entries.intro: 11/16/2641 6:55:00 AM The Argo Comms Log Transcript
entries.details: Cdre. Yu: "Well done, Smith. Given our shortage of Starcom vessels here, you and your ship will need to take on an outsized role for your experience." Cdre. Yu: "Until Starcom re-opens the wormhole and sends reinforcements, establishing an outpost is a lower priority than strengthening our defenses. I'm authorizing you to make full use of the resources recovered from the outpost to outfit The Argo. I'll talk to our research chief about getting you access to the lab as well." +150 Aluminum +8 Copper +6 Yttrium +1 Chiralite Cdre. Yu: "Unless there's anything else, I'll brief you on our next moves after you've had a chance to upgrade The Argo." Cmd Smith: No further questions.

entries.summary: Dr Rama: "I am Dr. Rama. I'm the head of Celaeno's Research projects. We've...
entries.intro: 11/16/2641 6:55:00 AM The Argo Comms Log Transcript
entries.details: Dr Rama: "I am Dr. Rama. I'm the head of Celaeno's Research projects. We've spent the past month studying the nearby artifact and looking for clues to its operation on nearby planets. Cdre Yu has just notified me that for "defense" reasons we're redirecting our priorities and I'm to place my lab at your disposal. Incidentally, that's a figure of speech, you are not to break anything." Cmd Smith: I'll do my best. Dr Rama: "I'd prefer you do nothing at all, but your best will suffice." Dr Rama: "Given my new directives, the object uncovered has given us some research data you can put to work. If you'll meet me in the lab, I can educate you on our facilities." Cmd Smith: Will do.

entries.summary: "Impressive. You didn't break anything."
entries.intro: The Argo: 2641.11.16 06:57 at 5.50 x 5.50 Unknown Space, Crew Log Entry
entries.details:
Dr Rama:

Impressive. You didn't break anything.

entries.summary: "This interface shows research technologies available. Use it to direct our..."
entries.intro: The Argo: 2641.11.16 06:57 at 5.50 x 5.50 Unknown Space, Crew Log Entry
entries.details:
Dr Rama:

This interface shows research technologies available. Use it to direct our computer's research.

I recommend at least researching "Turbo Thrust". It'll speed up your exploration significantly.

entries.summary: Cdre. Yu: "If The Argo is one of our only vessels in this space, you'll need...
entries.intro: 11/16/2641 6:55:00 AM The Argo Comms Log Transcript
entries.details: Cdre. Yu: "If The Argo is one of our only vessels in this space, you'll need a full command crew for maximum efficiency and to conduct planetary surveys." Cdre. Yu: "Some of the team members you evacuated from the outpost have volunteered. They've been added to your crew roster, which you can review at any time. They're admittedly a bit green, but I think with some experience they'll be officer material in no time. Speaking of experience..." Cdre. Yu: "We've detected some ship movement around a nearby gas giant. There also appears to be some activity on the surface of one of its moons. I want you to check it out. The ships have similar energy readings as the Red Raiders, so use those resources to get The Argo ready for combat. " Cmd Smith: Will do.

entries.summary: "Turbo thrust"
entries.intro: The Argo: 2641.11.16 07:41 at 5.63 x 5.42 Unknown Space, Crew Log Entry
entries.details:
Lt. Avery:

Turbo thrust!

This will speed things up. Watch our energy levels, though.

entries.summary: The anomaly is a partially buried ring-shaped artifact, roughly 100 meters...
entries.intro: 11/16/2641 7:50:00 AM The Argo Lander SCS-01 Planetary Anomaly Report at 5.64 x 5.43 Unknown Space
entries.details: The anomaly is a partially buried ring-shaped artifact, roughly 100 meters in diameter. While technologically advanced, the structure shows signs of a design in progress, suggesting that this was an experimental device or prototype. Cdt. Kepler (Observation Insight): The rocks and dirt nearby have undergone zero oxidation, so it was excavated quite recently. Cdt. Gliese observes that while the structure is much too large to transport, it has gold connectors leading to what appears to be a data storage component. If provided with power, it might be possible to access the data. +5 Gold The process turns out to be surprisingly tricky--the artifact reacts to energy from the lander in unexpected ways. With careful attention, Cdt. Gliese is able to keep the power high enough to extract the data, but not damage the artifact or the lander.

entries.summary: "The data recovered from the buried ring is an exotic mathematical..."
entries.intro: The Argo: 2641.11.16 08:23 at 5.64 x 5.43 Unknown Space, Crew Log Entry
entries.details:
Lt. Avery:

The data recovered from the buried ring is an exotic mathematical description of warp space. Possibly a coordinate system?

entries.summary: Dr Rama: "I've had an opportunity to examine the object our outpost team found
entries.intro: 11/16/2641 9:30:00 AM The Argo Comms Log Transcript
entries.details: Dr Rama: "I've had an opportunity to examine the object our outpost team found. As I suspected, the nearby artifact is a wormhole generator. The object we found allows us to communicate with it. The last piece of the puzzle I deduced from your team's investigation of the buried ring." Dr Rama: "Coordinates are encoded as mathematical formulae describing warp space. Knowing the particular formulae for a location acts as a kind of key. My hypothesis is that if we input this formula into the wormhole generator, it will create a wormhole to a distant point in space. We, meaning you, should test this hypothesis by activating the nearby artifact and entering its wormhole." Cmd Smith: And at that point will be another gateway we can use to return? Dr Rama: "Best case scenario, yes. Worst case, you'll end up light years away and have to trek back in normal space. And I'll have the lab back to myself. Be sure to pack some extra food."

entries.summary: Cdre. Yu: "The archaeological team has reported their findings to me. The...
entries.intro: 11/16/2641 9:30:00 AM The Argo Comms Log Transcript
entries.details: Cdre. Yu: "The archaeological team has reported their findings to me. The nearby ring artifact that Dr. Rama says can be used as a transport gateway was built by an entity or culture referred to as "the Remnants". Their technology may aid us in re-opening the wormhole from our side. In any event, it is far in advance of anything we have." Cdre. Yu: "Investigate the endpoint of this gateway. If you can find the source of these Red Raider ships, neutralize them if possible. But your top priority is to find any similar Remnant artifacts or technology. " Cmd Smith: We're on it. Cdre. Yu: "Was there anything else?" Cmd Smith: Why is this wormhole universe classified? Cdre. Yu: "That's a fair question. A whole new universe is a major discovery. We should want all Starcom divisions as well as the civilian sectors studying this space. There was a lot of arguing among the division heads on this topic." Cdre. Yu: "The final decision, as I've been informed, was that if the initial two-year research phase didn't uncover any serious threats here, Starcom would make a general announcement and expand exploration. I suspect recent events might change that timeline."

entries.summary: "I've marked the coordinates the equation points to on our map. Now let's see..."
entries.intro: The Argo: 2641.11.16 09:47 at 5.50 x 5.35 Unknown Space, Crew Log Entry
entries.details:
Lt. Avery:

I've marked the coordinates the equation points to on our map. Now let's see if that gateway will take us there. It'd be a long walk in normal space.

entries.summary: "Theres a natural layer of etherine not far from this planets core...."
entries.intro: The Argo: 2641.11.16 13:56 at 5.68 x 5.40 Unknown Space, Crew Log Entry
entries.details:
Cdt. Cassie Pirx (Astroscience):

Theres a natural layer of etherine not far from this planets core. Unfortunately the lander would be crushed far above that depth.

entries.summary: "The upper atmosphere of this planet is putting on quite a light show, but..."
entries.intro: The Argo: 2641.11.16 17:49 at 5.50 x 5.35 Unknown Space, Crew Log Entry
entries.details:
Cdt. Cassie Pirx (Astroscience):

The upper atmosphere of this planet is putting on quite a light show, but well outside the visual spectrum in the far UV range. This reveals some unusual aspects of solar radiation.
